messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
State Patrol, 9-1-1, we are on Minnesota Lake. Our boat has capsized.
Okay, is everybody above water?
Fairly.
What part of the lake are you on?
We're about a mile south of the landing.
Miles south of the landing? Can everyone swim?
One of us can't swim.
Do you have life preservers with you?
Yes, but we have to hang on to the boat for dear life.
Okay, I need to transfer you to Faribault County so they can send help. I'll stay on the line with you. How far offshore are you?
Approximately a mile.
A mile offshore or a mile from the landing?
A mile from the landing. Hi, State Patrol. I've got a boat that's capsized on Minnesota Lake about a mile south of the landing. Two people are hanging on, one cannot swim.
A mile south of the landing? Got it. I'll page fire and rescue.
Are they coming? We're getting tired.
Yes, they're on their way. Do you see any debris or something to help you float?
There's a red gas can approximately 10-15 feet north of us.
Okay, is there any wildlife nearby, like a refuge area?
Yes, we're in the middle of the wildlife refuge area.
Stay on the line, they're coming. How's your friend holding up?
He's keeping afloat, but it's getting harder.
Keep encouraging him. We'll stay with you as long as we can. If you need to put the phone down to help him, do it.
We don't see any houses around us, just open water.
Stay calm and keep holding on. Have you been able to grab anything else floating nearby?
No, just the gas can, but it's moving away from us.
Okay, I'll let you know when they are close. Do you have a jacket on?
We have one life jacket between us. I gave it to my friend.
Good. Keep holding on and stay calm. They're getting a boat into the water right now.
We're trying, but the water is very cold and it's getting really tough. We're drifting further south.
They're coming as quickly as they can. Do you see any lights from the rescue vehicles?
Yes, I see some lights.
They're getting closer. Just keep holding on and stay calm.
Okay, but we are freezing. Please, hurry!
They're almost there. I know it's tough, but stay with me and keep holding on.
I see a rescue truck coming towards us. We're directly in line with it.
That's great. Keep your eyes on it and keep holding on. They will be with you very soon.
We're both above water but just barely holding on.
Help is almost there. Stay strong, stay calm.
We're starting to lose strength. Where are they?
They're launching the boat now. Hang in there, Keith.
I see them! They're on the way.
Good, just keep holding on a little longer. You're doing great.
Okay. I hope they get here soon.
They're almost there. You're going to be okay. Just stay with me.
Got it. Thank you.
